		<div id="comment_body_64772482"><p><div class="quote"><p>I don't see a reasonable way for real meat-sack people to be able to actually verify who they are online without some degree of involvement from the state.</p></div><p>For a second there, smart card slots were becoming more common on PCs, I had them on several laptops. In theory anyone could issue you a card which you could slot into your computer and use it for both authentication of identity (you are the same person they handed the card to) and also as an encryption key. Then you'd supply a PIN to unlock the key. I also have a USB card reader around here someplace that was issued by some bank which I got with a mess of cables at a yard sale.</p><p>This requires only as much go<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64772482">

